3) Why I choose Candidate 1 and reject Candidate 2:
- I choose the Arena‑ready 1983 rock CD because the elements most central to my identity as a listener are present: multi‑tracked, layered electric guitars and stacked harmonies, concise AOR/rock songcraft, and a vocal‑forward presentation that supports strong lead singing and tight rhythm interplay. Those are core deciding features — guitar energy, multi‑part harmony and punchy, focused rock arrangements — that make a record feel like the classic‑rock/AOR albums I want to live with and dissect for ensemble detail and interlocking guitar parts.
