- Fleetwood Mac: Offers warm analog production, low compression, tactile midrange warmth, close expressive lead vocals (Stevie Nicks/Christine McVie), tight multi‑part harmonies, and cohesive start‑to‑finish sequencing with song‑serving textured arrangements. This addresses several of my preferences (analog warmth, midrange clarity, harmonies, cohesive LP sequencing) but emphasizes intimate, vocal‑forward presentation and textured arrangements that often foreground vocal interplay and songcraft over raw, electric‑guitar‑forward energy.
